Preheat your #oven{} to 210°C. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Chop one half into very small pieces and thinly slice the other. Keep separate. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @green chilli{1} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked and finely chopped) from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the @lamb mince{200%g} into a #bowl{} and add the @ground cumin{1}(ground), finely chopped red onion, @panko breadcrumbs{10}, half the garlic, half the parsley, half the mint and half the chilli. Add the @water{100%ml} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Use your hands to combine the ingredients, then shape into 3 small sausage shapes per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast in the oven until soft and golden, ~{16-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. When hot, add the koftas and brown on all sides, ~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, finish off your prep. Pop the onion slices into a bowl and add the @red wine vinegar{1}(red wine). Turn to coat in the vinegar. Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into small chunks) into small chunks. Trim the root from the @iceberg lettuce{1/2} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Mix the remaining garlic with @olive oil{}.

When the koftas are browned, lower the heat to medium and keep cooking for another ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn every ~{2%minutes} or so.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, spoon the garlicky oil over the @plain naan{2} breads and place on a baking tray. When the fries have ~{4%minutes} left, warm the naans in the oven for ~{3-4%minutes}. Get ready to serve!

Toss the lettuce and tomatoes through the pickled red onion slices and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Place a warm, garlicky naan on each plate. Share the salad between your naans. Top with the koftas and a sprinkling of the remaining mint, parsley and chilli. Finish with a drizzle of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Sprinkle the @za'atar{1} spice on the fries, toss to coat and serve alongside. Enjoy!